%I A394871 #23 Apr 19 2026 23:51:29
%S A394871 1,2,4,7,15,30,57,99
%N A394871 a(n) is the minimum number m such that if there are 2*n cards face down on a table that are labeled 1, 1, 2, 2, ..., n, n, then one can select m sets of n cards such that at least one set is labeled 1, 2, ..., n exactly.
%C A394871 Cards with the same label are indistinguishable.
%C A394871 a(n) is the minimum number of n-subsets of a 2*n-set S such that for every perfect matching of the complete graph on S, at least one of the chosen sets is a transversal (i.e., contains one vertex of each edge).
%H A394871 Yifan Xie, <a href="/A394871/a394871.py.txt">Python program</a>
%F A394871 a(n) <= 2^(n - 1).
%F A394871 a(n) >= a(n - 1)*(2*n - 1)/n.
%e A394871 Number the cards c_1, c_2, ..., c_{2*n}.
%e A394871 For n = 3, choose the sets {c_1, c_3, c_5}, {c_1, c_3, c_6}, {c_1, c_4, c_5}, {c_1, c_4, c_6}. If there are no transversals among these sets, then at least two of c_1, c_3, c_5 are labeled the same number. If c_1 and c_3 are both labeled k, then c_4, c_5, c_6 cannot be labeled k. Therefore, c_4 and c_5, c_4 and c_6 both have the same labels, which is a contradiction. Hence the 4 sets satisfy the conditions, and a(3) <= 4.
%o A394871 (Python) # See links.
%Y A394871 Cf. A001147.
%K A394871 nonn,more,new
%O A394871 1,2
